The paper proposes a technique for handling missing data using rough set computations. This technique falls under the umbrella of machine learning and data mining, which are covered by the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also deals with decision tables, which are a common tool in data mining and database management, making cs.DM and cs.DB likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents empirical results using real data, which suggests a potential application in information retrieval, making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
